commit.message:
Merge branch 'topic/java_api/bare_node_wrapping' into 'master'

Java API: Wrap node fields in structs

Closes #773

See merge request eng/libadalang/langkit!1039

Wrap node types struct fields in their Java Classes

Before this commit, node typed structure fields were stored as is in
Java structure wrapping classes. Entities were 'Entity' and bare node
were 'PointerWrapper'.
Now, those fields are stored as '<my_lang>Node' in their Java wrapping
classes.

Wrap/unwrap composite struct fields through their 'wrap/unwrap' methods

Before this commit, in Native Image bindings, composite struct fields
were wrapped and unwrapped in a flat way. This was really fishy and hard
to maintain.
Now we call 'wrap' and 'unwrap' methods to avoid this flattening step
and all resulting possible errors.

Make 'ni_field_unwrap' use the 'ni_write' function

Make the 'ni_write' function more generic to make it usable in the
'ni_field_unwrap' function and avoid unwrapping logic duplication.

Make 'ni_field_wrap' use the 'ni_wrap' function

Make Native Image value wrapping function more generic to avoid wrapping
logic duplication, then use it in the 'ni_field_wrap' function.

Add util functions about wrapped nodes in JNI

Add util functions in the JNI C stubs:
 * a function to create a wrapped node (inside its designated Java
   class) from an entity.
 * a function to get the entity from a wrapped node Java object.

Add 'equals' method on the 'Char' class

This method is required for a later commit, in the Java bindings tests.

Adapt symbol representation: store reference to symbol table

That'll allow us to go from (thin_symbol, sym_table) to symbol, and vice
versa, where with the old representation there was no other way to go
from symbol to thin than redoing a full-lookup.

That'll help us transition to thin-symbol storage everywhere.

Merge branch 'mr/pmderodat/lkt-fwd-ref-match-rule' into 'master'

Lkt lowering: fix token forward references in lexer match rules

See merge request eng/libadalang/langkit!1042

Lkt lowering: fix token forward references in lexer match rules

The order of rules in lexers is not meant to be significant. Since
"match" rules can refer to tokens, this means that it must be possible
to refer to a given token from a "match" rule even if that token is
defined later in the source code.

Lkt lowering was not supporting this so far: this commit plugs this
hole.

Merge branch 'mr/pmderodat/lkt-find-or-raise' into 'master'

Remove the ".find or_raise" composed attribute

See merge request eng/libadalang/langkit!1038

Remove the ".find or_raise" composed attribute

It is currently unused in both Lkt and Libadalang, has never been
tested, and will be somewhat obsolete with Lkt:

  X.find_or_raise(Y)

can be trivially written as:

  X.filter(Y)[0]
